Key Match Events: Darius Garland scored a go-ahead 3-pointer with 45 seconds left
The Cavs rallied down the stretch, outscoring the Bucks 18-8 over the final 6:06
Jarrett Allen had a huge block on Milwaukee's Damian Lillard in the final seconds
Mobley displayed his all-around game over a span of seven seconds in the second quarter
Post-Match Reflections: The Cavs also survived without Mitchell carrying them. He only scored one point after the first quarter, finishing with 14
The Bucks: Showed grit in giving all they had despite not having Antetokounmpo, who averages 31 points
The Cavaliers: Another good lesson to not take any team for granted
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cavs were just the second team in history to start 7-0 with every player averaging less than 30 minutes
